N. circuit, roundabout way, digression, detour, circumbendibus, ambages, loop
winding &c. (circuition)
zigzag &c. (deviation). V. perform a circuit
go round about, go out of one's way
make a detour
meander &c. (deviate). lead a pretty dance
beat about the bush
make two bites of a cherry. Adj. circuitous, indirect, roundabout
zigzag &c. (deviating)
backhanded. Adv. by a side wind, by an indirect course
in a roundabout way
from pillar to post.
